      • kDCLBlankable

        public static final java.lang.String kDCLBlankable
        The name of the attribute that signifies that a hidden field should not be blanked by the Dynamically Optional Clusters infrastructure. An example of where this is used is on the hidden field that represents the address header value e.g. 1|0|EN|EN|1|0|. The address infrastructure expects that this field will always be set, blanking it can cause form submission to fail.
